The Joint Admissions and Matriculation Board (JAMB) has announced that candidates with provisional admission offers should accept same through CAPS Mobile App as failure to do so could lead to forfeiture of admission. The admission agency, which made this announcement in a series of tweets on Tuesday, also said that the App could be downloaded from Google Play Store, “Candidates who have been offered PROVISIONAL ADMISSION BUT ARE YET TO ACCEPT the admission are  to immediately accept such offers free by using the CAPS Mobile App downloaded from the Google Play Store,” it tweeted. Jamb further explained that the CAPS Mobile App was designed to enable people accept admission offers without going out during the lockdown period.